main event: A radar operator observed an unidentified object moving erratically at varying altitudes between 1500 and 3000 feet over Ocean City, New Jersey on July 23, 1961.
interesting points: The object was observed both visually and on the radar scope for about 10 minutes.
The radar operator stated that this was not a normal target and that the lights and motion were unlike any known aircraft.
The object had flashing irregular lights and made sharp, erratic movements.
The object was described as a 'strong return' on the radar scope, suggesting it was a solid object.
The object finally faded from both visual and radar observation.
